 Hellas Verona squad, staff and directors have gone into self-isolation after Sampdoria striker Manolo Gabbiadini tested positive for Coronavirus. Gabbiadini played for an hour in the 2-1 Serie A win over Verona at Marassi at the weekend, a game that was played behind closed doors. In an updated statement, Verona announced they have taken all the necessary procedures to limit possible infection. That includes the squad, staff and directors who travelled to Genoa at the weekend going into self-isolation until March 22. Gabbiadini is the second Serie A player to test positive after Juventus defender Daniele Rugani. Juventus confirmed they have 121 people in self-isolation, including President Andrea Agnelli. 